Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setTieHiLoMode(25.10)                                    setTieHiLoMode(25.10)

Name
       setTieHiLoMode  -  Controls certain aspects of how the software adds or
       deletes tie-high and tie-low cells

Syntax
       setTieHiLoMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-cell {{tieHi1 tieLo1} {tieHi2 tieLo2} ...}]

       [-createHierPort {true | false}]

       [-honorDontTouch {true | false}]

       [-honorDontUse {true|false}]

       [-maxDistance <distanceValue>]

       [-maxFanout <fanOutValue>]

       [-modulePrevention {true | false}]

       [-prefix <prefixName>]

       [-reportHierPort {true | false}]

       Controls certain aspects of how the software adds or  deletes  tie-high
       and tie-low cells.

       See  getTieHiLoMode  to  query  current settings for the setTieHiLoMode
       command.

       The parameters of the setTieHiLoMode command affect the behavior of the
       following commands:

              * addTieHiLo

              * deleteTieHiLo

                Note: Parameters specified by addTieHiLo  and  deleteTieHighLo
                supersede those specified by the setTieHiLoMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setTieHiLoMode parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man setTieHiLoMode

       -cell {{tieHi1 tieLo1} {tieHi2 tieLo2} ...}
              Specifies the pairs of tie cells to be used  by  the  addTieHiLo
              command.

              You can specify a maximum of two tie-cells in a cell list, where
              one cell must be a tie-high driver, and the other a tie-low dri-
              ver.  If the current tie cell type does not have enough location
              to  place,  the  tool picks the next tie cell type in order from
              the pair list for connection and placement. If the last pair  of
              the  tie  cells  is not legal to be placed, it will still be in-
              serted. However, there will be overlapping with other  instance,
              and in such cases the tool will give an error message mentioning
              the need to run refinePlace.

              A  single  cell  with both tie connections, high and low, can be
              specified as below.

              setTieHiLoMode -cell {{TieHiLo1} {TieHiLo2} {TieHiLo3} ....}

              The software selects the nearest cell pair to make new tie  con-
              nections during the postMask flow.

              Default: "" (empty string)

       -createHierPort {true | false}
              Allows the added tie cells to connect to tie pins across hierar-
              chical  boundaries  if other constraints, such as maximum fanout
              and maximum distance, allow it.

              Default: false

       -honorDontTouch {true | false}
              Allows both addTieHiLo and deleteTieHiLo commands to  honor  the
              dont_touch property set on instances, nets, cells, and modules.

              Default: false

       -honorDontUse {true|false}
              Honors dont_use attribute on cells.

              Default: false

       -maxFanout <fanOutValue>
              Specifies the number of tie-pins a tie-net can drive. A value of
              0 implies no fanout constraint.

              Default: 0

       -maxDistance <distanceValue>
              Specifies  the  maximum  Manhattan distance, in microns, between
              the tie-cell driver and the tie-pins. A value of  0  implies  no
              distance constraint.

              Default: 0

       -modulePrevention {true|false}
              When  this parameter is set to true, the addTieHiLo command adds
              tie-cells for module instantiation port. Tie-cells may  also  be
              added  inside the module to tie the output port of the module so
              that module function can be prevented.

              Default: false

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies a prefix for the added tie-cell instances.

              Default: ""

       -reportHierPort {true | false}
              When the value of -createHierPort is true, reports created  port
              connections to a file named tiehilo.rpt.

              Default: false

       -reset Resets  parameters to their default values. The -reset parameter
              must be the first parameter specified. If you specify -reset  by
              itself,  the  software  resets  all setTieHiLoMode parameters to
              their default values. If you specify  parameters  after  -reset,
              the  software resets only those parameters to their default val-
              ues.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

Example
              * The  following  command  sets  TIEHI and TIELO cells a maximum
                distance of 20 microns between the tie-cell pin and  the  tie-
                off input pins and a tie-net can drive up to 10 tie-pins:

                setTieHiLoMode  -maxFanout  10  -maxDistance  20  -cell "TIEHI
                TIELO"

              * The following command resets the -maxDistance parameter to its
                default value:

                setTieHiLoMode -reset -maxDistance

              * The following command resets all setTieHiLoMode parameters  to
                their default values:

                setTieHiLoMode -reset

Related Information
